#5107
Mourners' Cart Track~
Uneven furrows lie like scars under your boots, and every pooled reflection shows a duskier sky than the one above you. Weatherworn icons hang from split posts beside the track, each one painted over with tar except for a single silver tear. Here in Mourners' Cart Track, the air tastes faintly metallic, and the back of your throat tightens each time the bellwind shifts through the hedgerows.~
