#5108
Fog-Soaked Furrow~
Rusted prayer stakes and cracked boundary stones crowd the path, each scratched with names that parish records no longer admit existed. You can hear grain whispering though no healthy crop remains, only brittle stalks that clatter together like rosary beads in a shaking hand. Fog-Soaked Furrow still bears old harvest markers, but each marker now points toward barrows, shrines, and sluices meant to guide processions of the dead.~
